AM_2EO3cvMHdgyRkJioPVzmIkSd5PHaaysTXKg_G5XXeMhEYtH_qm4InFz-Yq1yunQE5CLla73IFu19aj5HMrM-1T2n1epcdBOxKcEuuvu2I72vJdtwMM0dNa2hhtugXjTYxsAGMIPOMHzH8SiwvV53KIOilv4KQFBym3zMNPLdwNzM3UDtC3z3gbh9fF00dUFo4PwiqXjHXsAwWFgb5vKSEqHaDz06KNswAZtm9wA--f325zaCtSdnqJleVHzp2lYwf3MWm8lMeuyuAtEnuqNYN34rxBH8CmiQwEg1FaybGFvjNLn8VAatb2fW_EcPu1ZD2dqlA71L37bbVE4eubTlncXz9Qsh0AnwP5FEgGaKuZUwbnzyUS0XZWJSu4msZScfJKxUdo_wbmWtlGkTXslCaR_huXKISR85UcV8vj8KQcb1opwfdh39Ki00IEbWkpOnVZCMEXqUHTsh2nptj2sBzKBKUrtBT_BPW2z0wLGL9FtQUu-vZtIjyYcsH9EMtI=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class structure**\\n\\nI'm thinking about file class names and whether they should be one-to-one for top-level public tests. I wonder if we can add package-private top-level interfaces even though all top-level test classes must be public. It seems like we might avoid inner classes this way. One file could include these interfaces without special characters in their names. However, I'm debating if using nested structures might still be a better option for clarity.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing class loader issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the unrelated class loader interface definitions that were causing an owner issue, which we managed to fix. There’s a potential problem with `ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader()` in the Gradle worker; perhaps it's because there’s no Mockito in the classpath? However, the tests are running on the system app class loader. I need to ensure everything is clearly summarized and concise. Let’s refine this further!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the failing test by updating:\n\n`tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ProxyMockMakerInnerCommonClassLoaderTest.java`\n\nRoot cause: the custom `InterfaceOnlyClassLoader` delegated all non-owned classes to the platform class loader, so Mockito’s `MockNameImpl` could not resolve the enclosing test class while calling `Class#getSimpleName()` on the nested interface.\n\nChange made:\n- Each custom loader now:\n  - loads only its assigned interface itself,\n  - explicitly rejects the opposite interface to keep `CommonClassLoader` fallback coverage,\n  - delegates all other classes to the system class loader.\n\nThis should preserve coverage of both `CommonClassLoader.loadClass` call sites while avoiding the `NoClassDefFoundError`.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01e3eac1d706ac8e016a3aa173993c8193ba13a74f71ceefe1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 460, "output": 740, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35504, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782227297647, "responseId": "resp_01e3eac1d706ac8e016a3aa16239b88193abaa150ccfa3d0bf"}, "toolResults": []}
